  "prompt": "What is the weather in orlando like in January?",
  "response": "In January, Orlando, Florida, experiences mild and generally pleasant weather, which is one of the reasons it's a popular time for tourists to visit. Here\u2019s what you can typically expect:\n\n**Temperature:**\n- **Average High:** Around 72\u00b0F (22\u00b0C)\n- **Average Low:** Around 51\u00b0F (11\u00b0C)\n\n**Weather Conditions:**\n- **Sunshine:** Orlando enjoys plenty of sunshine in January, with an average of 7 hours of sunshine per day.\n- **Rainfall:** January is one of the drier months in Orlando, with an average rainfall of about 2.3 inches (58 mm). Rain usually comes in the form of brief showers.\n- **Humidity:** Humidity levels are relatively moderate compared to the summer months, making it more comfortable.\n\n**Other Considerations:**\n- **Clothing:** Light layers are recommended, as it can be cooler in the mornings and evenings but warmer during the day.\n- **Wind:** Gentle breezes are common, with average wind speeds around 8 mph (13 km/h).\n\nOverall, January is a great time to visit Orlando if you prefer cooler and less humid weather compared to the hot and sticky summer months. It\u2019s ideal for exploring theme parks, outdoor activities, and other attractions comfortably.",
